 EXHIBITION

 Till October 31 at Soumya?s Creation, 57/9 Ballygunge Circular Road; 10 am - 7 pm: A getting-ready-for-Diwali showing of costume jewellery (ranging from beads and costume to more traditional ethnic pieces) and home accessories (candles, durries, ceramic, wrought iron, framed pictures, wooden trays, etc.). The candles are produced by Silence, an organisation for the physically challenged. Also, bags made by deaf and dumb school children as part of their vocational training activity under Suman Saraogi. 

 Till October 31 at Artisana, 13 Chowringhee Terrace, 1st floor; 10 am - 7.30 pm: Crafts Council of West Bengal presents an exhibition of terracotta lamps and garden accessories, and textiles and natural dye cotton fabrics. 

 Till November 1 at Shahid Minar grounds; 9 am - 12 midnight: Annual Bazi Bazaar organised by Burrabazar Fire Works Dealers? Association. 

 Till November 4 at Sasha Shop, 27 Mirza Ghalib Street; 10 am - 7 pm; Sunday (10 am - 1 pm): Sasha, an NGO and founder member of Fair Trade Forum, presents The Festival of Lights, an exhibition celebrating the spirit of Diwali through carved dokra and wrought iron diyas and candle stands from Orissa and Bastar, terracotta candle stands, a wide selection of diyas, candles, bamboo lights and other Diwali paraphernalia. 

 FESTIVAL

